ng money.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Since the Chinese market was so nascent, the Al=
ibaba team realized it couldn&#8217;t just copy the US business model of ch=
arging businesses to list and taking a cut of transactions. Instead, Alibab=
a gave away the product and transactions for free and charged sellers for b=
etter placement. It worked.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">For the first time, in early =
2002, Alibaba turned a profit. Just when things were looking up, though, Al=
ibaba would face two of its biggest challenges yet.</p><p style=3D"color: #=
